# Backend conventions

- **Routers are thin.** `app/api/` handles HTTP only; all logic lives in
  `app/services/`. A router should validate input, call a service, render/return.
- **Services are pure-ish.** Pipeline services (parser/merge/generator) take typed
  inputs and return typed outputs. No FastAPI imports inside services.
- **Models vs schemas.** SQLAlchemy models in `app/models/`; Pydantic request/response
  schemas alongside. Don't leak ORM objects into templates — pass schemas/dicts.
- **Config via `app/core/config.py`** (pydantic-settings, env-driven). No literals for
  paths, secrets, branding.
- **Storage only through `app/core/storage.py`.** Never call `open()` / build paths in
  routers or services directly — go through the `Storage` interface so Nextcloud can
  drop in later.
- **DB sessions** via the dependency in `app/core/db.py`. One session per request.
- Every schema change ships an **Alembic migration** in the same change.
- Type-hint everything. Prefer explicit over clever.
